    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for pacemaker.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The Pacemaker cluster resource manager is a collection of technologies\nworking together to maintain data integrity and application availability in\nthe event of failures.\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):\n\n* pacemaker seems to end up in an unfence loop (BZ#1972273)\n\n* On a three-node cluster if two nodes are hard-reset, sometimes the\ncluster ends up with unremovable transient attributes (BZ#1989622)\n\n* Pacemaker fencer should retry failed meta-data commands (BZ#1992014)\n\n* [RFE] Add ability to use sbd on cluster nodes but not remote nodes\n(BZ#1993891)\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
